@MetaschemaAssembly(formalName="Role", description="Defines a function, which might be assigned to a party in a specific situation.", name="role", moduleClass=OscalMetadataModule.class, remarks="Permissible values to be determined closer to the application (e.g. by a receiving authority).\n\nOSCAL has defined a set of standardized roles for consistent use in OSCAL documents. This allows tools consuming OSCAL content to infer specific semantics when these roles are used. These roles are documented in the specific contexts of their use (e.g., responsible-party, responsible-role). When using such a role, it is necessary to define these roles in this list, which will then allow such a role to be referenced.") public static class Metadata.Role extends Object implements gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IBoundObject
